quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  3,42,"And when the angels said, \"O Maryam ! Allah has certainly chosen you and cleaned you and chosen you above the women of the worlds"
  3,43,O Maryam! be devoutly obedient to your Fosterer and prostrate and bow down with those who bow down
  3,44,"That is from the news of the unseen (which) We communicate to you, and you were not with them when they cast their pens* (to know) which of them should be the guardian of Maryam nor were you with them when they disputed (about this issue). * Lots"
  3,45,"When the angels said, \"O Maryam! certainly, Allah conveys to you the good news of a word from Him, his name is the Messiah, Isa, the son of Maryam, worthy of regard in the world and the hereafter, and from among those who are near (to Allah)"
  3,46,"And he will talk to human beings (while) in the cradle and (in) old age, and (he will be) from among the righteous"
  3,47,"(She) said, \"O My Fosterer ! how can I have a son when man has not touched me?\" He said, \"Like that, Allah creates what He wills, when He decrees an affair then, He says to only, \"Be,\" so it is. it is"
  3,48,And He will teach him the book and wisdom and the Torah and the Injeel
  3,49,"and (he will be) a messenger sent to the children of Israel, (saying) that: I have come to you with a sign from your Fosterer, that I make for you from clay, a figure like that of a bird, then I blow into it, so it becomes a bird by the permission of Allah; and I heal the blind by birth and the leper and I bring to life the dead by Allah's permission and I inform you of that which you eat and that which you store in your houses; in that there is certainly a sign for you if you are believers"
  3,50,"And I am a testifier for that which is before me of the Torah, and (I have come) to make lawful for you something of that which was forbidden to you and I have come to you with a sign from your Fosterer so fear Allah and obey me"
  3,51,"Allah is certainly my Fosterer and your Fosterer, so serve Him, this is the straight path"
  3,52,"So when Isa perceived infidelity from them, (he) said, \"Who will be my helpers for (the sake of) Allah.\" The disciples said, \"We are Allah's helpers, we believe in Allah and you bear witness that we have submitted (as Muslims)"
  3,53,"Our Fosterer ! we believe in that which you have sent down and we follow the messenger, so record us with those who bear witness"
  3,54,So they planned and Allah planned (too) and Allah is the Best of planners